posts.author: hh01
posts.title: Chris Cummings, Chief Executive Officer of the Investment Association said:
posts.text:
search: Chris Cummings, Chief Executive Officer of the Investment Association said: 
We are delighted to welcome the government’s new, ambitious Investment Management Strategy. This strategy will give asset management firms, who collectively manage the pensions of millions of British households and hold the UK’s biggest listed companies to account, a roadmap to success through Brexit and beyond. 
Together with the Asset Management Taskforce, this comprehensive strategy provides the opportunity for partnership between Government, industry and regulators to ensure the UK remains the leading European asset management centre. The forward-looking agenda brings a welcome focus on the critical success factors of tomorrow, including harnessing the fintech revolution, encouraging sustainable investment and ensuring a diverse and world-leading workforce. Domestic excellence will help to boost the industry’s export and trade contribution as the UK looks to a new place in the world. This strategy means our industry will continue to deliver the best possible outcomes for savers and for the UK economy in the years to come.

>>97330675
This episode was disappointing this had a lot of potential to end a fairly polarizing season with a bang. There were so many problems.
>Kyle not getting called out for his actions from the last episode by the kids. Only Ike having any reaction to this.
>Heidi being the focus while with the kids. With the boys doing nothing.
>The "White's" joke being too on the nose.
>Boring return to status quo.
This had a lot of good things going with it like they could have done so many things!
>Have the kids resent Kyle or just not communicate with him. Make it so they go with him just to find Ike, not to help him. They also have 2 Cartmans in the group, they could throw jokes with them reacting to the event, or even reference past episodes in which Cartman did horrible or similar things to others. The boy's reactions and thoughts on Kyle should have been the focus.
>Have Hedi reach a point naturally throughout the episode that Cartman is a garbage person and that they should break up. Don't make this the focus of the kid's plot, have it happen subtly. More of the ghost Hedi or maybe if they joked more about the horrible things Eric's done she starts to recognize what's she's become and how close she is to doing those same things.
>To have it return to the status quo make it harsh. Have Hedi breaking up with Cartman be a bad one, tears, genuine anger, maybe Eric throws a punch, etc. Or if you want to push it darker make it so she believes there is no way to go back to the way things were and she kills herself, the show returns to the status quo via. a tragedy no one wants to remember the time a child killed themselves and the time a child helped kill millions of people so they move past it. Both of these could also put some development for Cartman and Kyle.( >>97330846 )
>Add Kenny and give him funny lines. Don't put Creek in if you're not going to try and do something with them.
4/10, easily this episode could have been so much more.

posts.author: randyv19
posts.title: Message Not Sent
posts.text:
In attempting to send to a .mil email address I get this message:
Message not sent; The following addresses were not accepted: {0} SCC-1203
I can see by previous posts in the forums that this is not a new issue for Comcast, going back to 2012. I had no problem with sending emails to the domain I referenced until last week. I spent a considerable amount of time on the phone with Comcast trying to troubleshoot this issue, to ultimately be told that the workorder would have to be elevated to the next level. I got a call last night telling me that the issue has been solved, however the issue hasn't been solved as of this morning.
Does anyone in this forum have any suggestions, short of finding another email service?

posts.text:
THREAD GUIDELINES
>Provide references for requested characters and keep them to one image/post.
>Keep requests /co/ related and keep them concise.
>General OC discussion belongs in "Work on your art" and the Donut Steel threads.
>However, OC requests are allowed as long as they aren't /trash/ material or fanfiction. If it's not /coc/ you must provide a link to the comic or cartoon.
>Be patient and take it easy! Don't forget to check the booru to see if your request was filled.
>Drawfriends, don't hold back.
>DON'T REPLY TO TROLLS OR WHINERS.
>Keep art critique short, otherwise take it to the Batman thread.
>No one is entitled to a request delivery.
>Don't fight spam with spam.
>No begging.
>Have fun!
>Collection of Deliveries:
http://the-collection.booru.org/ind ex.php?page=post&s=list
>Drawfriends Gallery List:
https://pastebin.com/ME97wvgq
>Drawing Books, tutorials, practice websites, and drawing programs:
http://pastebin.com/4CpXsY7a
NSFW deliveries and Requests should be posted in the >>>/aco/drawthread
